 MRS Felicia Olukemi Sarumi, the wife of a former Managing Director of the Nigerian Ports Authority, Adebayo Sarumi, is dead. She died on Friday, 16th October, 2020 after a brief illness, according to a statement by the former NPA MD. Sarumi, who is the Parakoyi of Ibadan Land, said the remains of his wife would be interred on a date to be announced later this month. “I lost my wife, my darling, my heart-warming desire left this sinful world to be with her creator on 16th October 2020,” he said. “As much I would love to have my wife with me for the next 30 years, I cannot question the omnipotent, omniscience and omnipresence God who has decided to take her away to be with him,” he added. 